## Styling with sxStyles - Centralized Approach

ALWAYS use `sxStyles` helper for complex styling - only use inline sx for minor margin/padding adjustments.

```tsx
import { sxStyles, combineStyles } from "types/commonTypes"

// âœ… CENTRALIZED STYLES OBJECT
const styles = sxStyles({
   container: {
      color: "text.primary",           // theme.palette.text.primary
      backgroundColor: "primary.50",   // theme.palette.primary[50]
      borderColor: "neutral.200",      // theme.palette.neutral[200]
      p: 2,
      borderRadius: 1
   },
   header: {
      color: "primary.main",
      mb: 2,
      // Responsive values with custom breakpoints
      fontSize: { xs: "1.2rem", tablet: "1.5rem", desktop: "1.8rem" },
      // Pseudo-selectors
      "&:hover": { backgroundColor: "primary.light" },
      "&:focus": { outline: "2px solid", outlineColor: "primary.main" },
      // Custom media queries with theme breakpoints
      [theme => theme.breakpoints.up('mobile')]: { textAlign: "left" },
      [theme => theme.breakpoints.down('tablet')]: { textAlign: "center" }
   },
   card: {
      // Responsive padding with custom breakpoints
      p: { xs: 1, mobile: 2, desktop: 3 },
      borderRadius: 2,
      // Child selectors
      "& svg": { 
         width: 20, 
         height: 20, 
         color: "neutral.600",
         // Responsive icon sizing
         [theme => theme.breakpoints.up('desktop')]: { width: 24, height: 24 }
      },
      "& .MuiTypography-root": { color: "text.secondary" }
   },
   iconButton: {
      // Theme function (when needed)
      backgroundColor: theme => theme.brand.white[100],
      border: theme => `1px solid ${theme.palette.neutral[200]}`,
      "&:disabled": { opacity: 0.5 }
   }
})

// âœ… USAGE IN JSX
<Box sx={styles.container}>
   <Typography variant="brandedH3" sx={styles.header}>Title</Typography>
   <Card sx={styles.card}>Content</Card>
   <IconButton sx={styles.iconButton}>Icon</IconButton>
</Box>

// âœ… MINOR ADJUSTMENTS ONLY (inline sx)
<Typography variant="medium" sx={{ mb: 1, pt: 0.5 }}>Text</Typography>

// âœ… COMBINING STYLES
sx={combineStyles([styles.base, isActive && styles.active], customSx)}
sx={[styles.icon, isMobile && styles.iconMobile]} // Array syntax
```

## Custom Breakpoints Reference

Available breakpoints from `packages/config-mui/breakpoints.ts`:

```tsx
// Standard MUI breakpoints
xs: 0       // Extra small devices (phones)
sm: 600     // Small devices (large phones)
md: 900     // Medium devices (tablets)
lg: 1280    // Large devices (desktops)
xl: 1920    // Extra large devices

// Custom CareerFairy breakpoints
lsCardsGallery: 648    // Livestream cards gallery
mobile: 768            // Mobile devices
tablet: 1023           // Tablet devices  
desktop: 1920          // Desktop devices
sparksFullscreen: 989  // Sparks fullscreen mode

// Usage patterns:
// 1. Breakpoint objects (preferred)
sx={{ width: { xs: "100%", mobile: "75%", tablet: "50%", desktop: "33%" } }}

// 2. Theme breakpoint functions
sx={{ [theme => theme.breakpoints.up('mobile')]: { display: 'flex' } }}
sx={{ [theme => theme.breakpoints.down('tablet')]: { fontSize: '14px' } }}
sx={{ [theme => theme.breakpoints.between('mobile', 'desktop')]: { p: 2 } }}

// 3. Only with specific custom breakpoints
sx={{ [theme => theme.breakpoints.up('lsCardsGallery')]: { gridColumns: 3 } }}
sx={{ [theme => theme.breakpoints.down('sparksFullscreen')]: { height: '50vh' } }}
```

